DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN FOUND DEAD IN DESERT NEAR PALMDALE 
Sheriff's detectives were investigating the apparent homicide of a man whose 
nude body was found Saturday in the desert near Palmdale, authorities said. 
The body was discovered by a passer-by about 12:15 p.m. near the intersection 
of Tierra Subida Avenue and Avenue S, Deputy Patrick Hunter of the Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Department said. Investigators have been unable to determine 
the cause of death, the identity or race of the victim or how long the body had 
been there. 
Hunter said an autopsy has been scheduled to determine the cause of death, and 
detectives were seeking information from the public concerning the slaying. 
